content.text:
Great! This one took you
${window.ExampleTime} seconds.

Now that we are familiar with the searching task,
let's introduce the estimation part. 
In the next screen, you will try to predict how fast
you can find a target in a field of distractors.

You will notice that the bonus depends on your
time estimation. the faster you predict you will find the 
target, the higher the bonus will be. However, the 
bonus is given only if finding the target (later, in the 
searching part) does not take you longer than you 
estimated (in the estimation part).
